## Key Technical Decisions

### 1. Static Site Architecture

**Decision**: Use static HTML/CSS/JavaScript (Webflow export)

**Rationale**:
- Simple deployment and hosting
- Fast page loads
- No backend dependencies
- Easy to maintain and update

**Implementation**: All pages are static HTML files with linked CSS and JavaScript

### 2. CSS Variable System for Brand Colors

**Decision**: Use CSS custom properties (variables) for all brand colors

**Rationale**:
- Ensures brand consistency across all pages
- Easy to update colors globally
- Maintains design system integrity

**Implementation**:
```css
:root {
  --beige: #efe0cb; /* Velvet Cream */
  --b100: #efe9dd; /* Soft Beige */
  --brown: #3f2823; /* Royal Cocoa */
  --accent-green: #142821; /* Deep Velvet Green */
  --vip-wine: #500b0c; /* Vintage Wine */
}
```

### 3. Image Organization Strategy

**Decision**: Organize images by purpose in subdirectories

**Rationale**:
- Clear file structure
- Easy to locate and update images
- Maintains separation of concerns

**Structure**:
```
/images
  /products - Product images
  /services - Service images
  /team - Team photos
  /philosophy - Philosophy section visuals
  / - General brand assets (logos, icons, hero)
```

### 4. Responsive Image Implementation

**Decision**: Use responsive image sets with srcset attributes

**Rationale**:
- Optimizes performance across devices
- Serves appropriate image sizes
- Maintains visual quality

**Pattern**:
```html
<img srcset="image-500w.jpg 500w, image-800w.jpg 800w, image-1080w.jpg 1080w" 
     sizes="(max-width: 507px) 100vw, 507px" 
     src="image.jpg">
```

### 5. CSS Filter for Team Images

**Decision**: Apply grayscale filter via CSS rather than converting image files

**Rationale**:
- Maintains original color images for flexibility
- Easy to toggle or modify
- No need to maintain duplicate image sets

**Implementation**:
```css
.material-flex .zoom-image {
  filter: grayscale(100%) !important;
}
```

## Design Patterns

### 1. Split-Screen Layouts

**Pattern**: Hero sections use split-screen design with image on one side, content on the other

**Usage**: Homepage hero, menu overlay

**Benefits**: Creates visual interest and elegant presentation

### 2. Full-Screen Menu Overlay

**Pattern**: Menu opens as full-screen overlay with brand messaging

**Implementation**: JavaScript-controlled visibility with smooth transitions

**Benefits**: Immersive navigation experience that reinforces brand

### 3. Tabbed Content Interface

**Pattern**: Philosophy section uses tabbed interface for multiple content views

**Usage**: Homepage philosophy section (Calm, Balance, Authenticity)

**Benefits**: Organizes content without overwhelming the user

### 4. Image Gallery with Zoom

**Pattern**: Product and team images use zoom effects on hover

**Implementation**: CSS transforms and transitions

**Benefits**: Interactive element that adds depth to static images

### 5. Consistent Header/Footer

**Pattern**: All pages share the same header and footer components

**Benefits**: Consistent navigation and branding across site

